<font color=#FFFF2D>By its order.</font>

7
00:02:17,810 --> 00:02:21,000
<font color=#FFFF2D>It's okay. Come back to me.</font>

8
00:02:21,001 --> 00:02:22,895
<font color=#FFFF2D>Come back to me.</font>

9
00:02:23,930 --> 00:02:25,833
<font color=#FFFF2D>Come back to me.</font>

10
00:02:25,834 --> 00:02:27,334
<font color=#FFFF2D>Stick em up!</font>

11
00:02:28,619 --> 00:02:31,823
<font color=#FFFF2D>You are the sheriff in this here town?</font>

12
00:02:32,715 --> 00:02:35,735
<font color=#FFFF2D>My tickle guns are gonna get you!</font>

13
00:02:37,008 --> 00:02:40,705
<font color=#FFFF2D>You want me to chase you? You better run.</font>

14
00:02:43,905 --> 00:02:46,905
<font color=#00FF40>(Kid giggling)</font>

15
00:02:59,853 --> 00:03:02,298
<font color=#FFFF2D>I remember moments in the middle.</font>

16
00:03:05,675 --> 00:03:07,262
<font color=#FFFF2D>I love you.</font>

17
00:03:08,063 --> 00:03:09,663
<font color=#FFFF2D>I hate you!</font>

18
00:03:21,809 --> 00:03:23,603
<font color=#FFFF2D>And this was the end.</font>

19
00:03:31,904 --> 00:03:33,763
<font color=#FFFF2D>Come back to me.</font>

20
00:03:34,469 --> 00:03:36,564
<font color=#FFFF2D>Baby, come back to me.</font>

21
00:03:52,012 --> 00:03:55,573
<font color=#FFFF2D>And now Im not so sure I believe in
beginnings and endings.</font>

22
00:03:56,523 --> 00:04:00,395
<font color=#FFFF2D>There are days that define
your story beyond your life.</font>

23
00:04:01,923 --> 00:04:04,078
<font color=#FFFF2D>Like the day they arrived.</font>

24
00:04:16,579 --> 00:04:17,101
<font color=#FFFF2D>Good Morning.</font>

25
00:04:21,393 --> 00:04:22,962
<font color=#FFFF2D>Where is everyone?</font>

26
00:04:24,967 --> 00:04:27,236
<font color=#FFFF2D>Ok... Well let's get started.</font>

27
00:04:27,237 --> 00:04:30,134
<font color=#FFFF2D>Today, we're talking about Portuguese</font>

28
00:04:30,135 --> 00:04:34,033
<font color=#FFFF2D>and why it sounds so different
from the other Romance languages.</font>

29
00:04:34,812 --> 00:04:39,532
<font color=#FFFF2D>The story of Portuguese begins
in the Kingdom of Galicia...</font>

30
00:04:39,732 --> 00:04:41,332
<font color=#00FF40>(cellphone ringing)</font>

31
00:04:42,329 --> 00:04:43,038
<font color=#FFFF2D>In the Middle Ages...</font>

32
00:04:43,711 --> 00:04:48,325
<font color=#FFFF2D>when a language was seen
as an expression of art.</font>

33
00:04:49,025 --> 00:04:52,025
<font color=#00FF40>(cellphone ringing)</font>

34
00:04:54,921 --> 00:04:56,834
<font color=#FFFF2D>Any news you want to share?</font>

35
00:04:57,235 --> 00:05:01,058
<font color=#FFFF2D>Dr. Banks can turn you turn the TV to
the news channel?</font>

36
00:05:18,009 --> 00:05:20,930
<font color=#00FF40>(news on tv)... But police have already
set up a perimeter around the area</font>

37
00:05:20,931 --> 00:05:23,671
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>As you can see, we got just
about as close as we can...</font></i>

38
00:05:23,672 --> 00:05:27,842
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>but unfortunately, Montana right now,
is on complete lock down.</font></i>

39
00:05:28,353 --> 00:05:30,926
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>The object apparently touched down...</font></i>

40
00:05:30,927 --> 00:05:33,757
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>40 minutes ago, just north of ****** 04.</font></i>

41
00:05:34,057 --> 00:05:38,099
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>We are waiting to hear if this is perhaps
an experimental vessel or...</font></i>

42
00:05:39,279 --> 00:05:40,941
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>Hold on...</font></i>

43
00:05:40,942 --> 00:05:44,183
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>Im learning that more objects like this</font></i>

44
00:05:44,184 --> 00:05:48,788
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>Have landed in as many as eight other
locations around the world</font></i>

45
00:05:48,789 --> 00:05:50,189
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>Yes? Henry?</font></i>

46
00:05:50,790 --> 00:05:54,080
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>This is from a site in Hokkaido.</font></i>

47
00:05:54,551 --> 00:05:57,989
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>This is worldwide and is
happening right now.</font></i>

48
00:05:58,270 --> 00:06:01,470
<i><font color=#00FF40>(Alarms going off)</font></i>

49
00:06:03,670 --> 00:06:06,382
<font color=#FFFF2D>Okay...um...</font>

50
00:06:07,083 --> 00:06:09,246
<font color=#FFFF2D>Class is dismissed.</font>

51
00:06:18,346 --> 00:06:20,846
<i><font color=#00FF40>(Aircraft flying by)</font></i>

52
00:06:57,090 --> 00:06:59,488
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>The Pentagon is simply asking
for cooperation</font></i>

53
00:06:59,489 --> 00:07:01,945
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>while authorities assess the object.</font></i>

54
00:07:01,946 --> 00:07:03,395
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>You are saying its not ours?</font></i>

55
00:07:03,396 --> 00:07:06,649
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>- Do you even know if its from Earth?
- We are collecting information.</font></i>

56
00:07:06,650 --> 00:07:08,436
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>We're coordinating with other countries.</font></i>

57
00:07:08,437 --> 00:07:11,924
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>We are not the only ones to
have one of these in our backyard.</font></i>

58
00:07:12,705 --> 00:07:15,634
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>If this is some kind of
peaceful first contact,</font></i>

59
00:07:15,635 --> 00:07:19,004
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>why send twelve? Why not just one?</font></i>

60
00:07:42,548 --> 00:07:43,948
<font color=#FFFF2D>I do not know, Mom.</font>

61
00:07:43,949 --> 00:07:46,142
<font color=#FFFF2D>Im watching the same news you are.</font>

62
00:07:50,272 --> 00:07:53,581
<font color=#FFFF2D>Mom...mom, please don't bother
with that channel.</font>

63
00:07:53,582 --> 00:07:56,841
<font color=#FFFF2D>How many times I have to say that
those people are idiots?</font>

64
00:07:59,904 --> 00:08:01,968
<font color=#FFFF2D>Do I sound nervous?</font>

65
00:08:03,102 --> 00:08:05,238
<font color=#FFFF2D>Ok, exactly...so...</font>

66
00:08:06,139 --> 00:08:09,917
<font color=#FFFF2D>Yeah, me? You know me. Im about the same</font>

67
00:08:14,651 --> 00:08:16,193
<font color=#FFFF2D>Mom, I'm fine.</font>

68
00:08:17,534 --> 00:08:20,379
<font color=#FFFF2D>Ok, I'll call you later - bye.</font>

69
00:08:29,280 --> 00:08:32,024
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>And in around eight hours after landing,</font></i>

70
00:08:32,025 --> 00:08:35,309
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>Theres still no signs of what
might be called "first contact."</font></i>

71
00:08:35,310 --> 00:08:39,030
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>The objects measuring
at least 1500ft tall...</font></i>

72
00:08:39,031 --> 00:08:42,476
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>...Two more have reported to
have penetrated Russian airspace.</font></i>

73
00:08:42,477 --> 00:08:46,832
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>One in Siberia and the other
on the coast of the Black Sea...</font></i>

74
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:50,850
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>...above the ocean. So far there are 12
unidentified objects spread across the globe...</font></i>

75
00:08:50,851 --> 00:08:53,636
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>...there is no obvious logic
to their locations</font></i>

76
00:08:53,637 --> 00:08:56,309
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>And no evidence that the
ships are even occ...</font></i>

77
00:08:56,310 --> 00:09:00,605
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>...entertain the idea that
if it is a kind of vessel,</font></i>

78
00:09:00,606 --> 00:09:02,495
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>it may be unmanned.</font></i>

79
00:09:02,496 --> 00:09:06,573
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>Regardless, we have a protocol
for scenarios like this.</font></i>

80
00:09:16,185 --> 00:09:19,185
<b><font color=#C752ED>LIVE FROM VENEZUELA</font></b>

81
00:10:01,385 --> 00:10:04,385
<i><font color=#00FF40>(Footsteps)</font></i>

82
00:10:14,300 --> 00:10:16,116
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>After two days' of extraordinary events,</font></i>

83
00:10:16,317 --> 00:10:19,003
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>the President this morning, has declared
a state of emergency</font></i>

84
00:10:19,004 --> 00:10:24,003
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>With as many as 5,000 National Guard being
deployed to the state of Montana, alone.</font></i>

85
00:10:24,004 --> 00:10:26,199
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>Borders are closed and flights
have been grounded,</font></i>

86
00:10:26,299 --> 00:10:27,399
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>stranding millions of travelers.</font></i>

87
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:31,612
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>gas, water and food continues to escalate</font></i>

88
00:10:31,613 --> 00:10:34,723
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>and federal authorities
have temporarily lifted</font></i>

89
00:10:34,724 --> 00:10:37,023
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>the overtime limit on law enforcement.</font></i>

90
00:10:37,424 --> 00:10:40,620
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>The ATF has put a temporary
ban on new gun licenses,</font></i>

91
00:10:40,621 --> 00:10:42,498
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>forcing many independent suppliers</font></i>

92
00:10:42,499 --> 00:10:44,525
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>of hunting equipment and firearms</font></i>

93
00:10:44,526 --> 00:10:46,711
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>to close their doors to the public.</font></i>

94
00:10:46,712 --> 00:10:49,453
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>48 hours later and no further development...</font></i>

95
00:10:49,454 --> 00:10:51,074
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>Two days.</font></i>

96
00:10:51,975 --> 00:10:54,807
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>And the public now expects us
to know all the answers.</font></i>

97
00:10:56,057 --> 00:10:57,905
<font color=#FFFF2D>I'm Colonel G.T. Weber.</font>

98
00:10:59,506 --> 00:11:01,406
<font color=#FFFF2D>We havn't formally met,
but two years ago,</font>

99
00:11:01,407 --> 00:11:04,221
<font color=#FFFF2D>You did a Farsi translation
for the Italians?</font>

100
00:11:05,072 --> 00:11:07,607
<font color=#FFFF2D>You made quick work on those
insurgent videos.</font>

101
00:11:07,608 --> 00:11:10,024
<font color=#FFFF2D>And you made quick work
with those insurgents.</font>

102
00:11:12,304 --> 00:11:14,004
<font color=#FFFF2D>You're on top...</font>

103
00:11:14,505 --> 00:11:17,374
<font color=#FFFF2D>on everyone's list
when it comes to translations.</font>

104
00:11:17,775 --> 00:11:21,500
<font color=#FFFF2D>And yet youve been two years in the SSBI.</font>

105
00:11:21,501 --> 00:11:24,053
<font color=#FFFF2D>So, you still have top secret clearance.</font>

106
00:11:24,054 --> 00:11:26,936
<font color=#FFFF2D>So thats why I'm in your office
and not in Berkeley.</font>

107
00:11:27,852 --> 00:11:29,406
<font color=#FFFF2D>Okay?</font>

108
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:40,167
<font color=#FFFF2D>I have something I need you
to translate for me.</font>

109
00:11:46,026 --> 00:11:48,526
<i><font color=#00FF40>(Recording plays)</font></i>

110
00:11:48,726 --> 00:11:50,376
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>Why are you here?</font></i>

111
00:11:53,492 --> 00:11:56,034
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>Can you understand us?</font></i>

112
00:12:03,750 --> 00:12:05,673
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>Where did you come from?</font></i>

113
00:12:14,085 --> 00:12:17,848
<font color=#FFFF2D>Now you heard...
what you make of it?</font>

114
00:12:20,916 --> 00:12:24,257
<font color=#FFFF2D>- Is that...?
- Yes.</font>

115
00:12:26,442 --> 00:12:29,679
<font color=#FFFF2D>- How many?
- How many what?</font>

116
00:12:29,680 --> 00:12:32,986
<font color=#FFFF2D>How many were speaking?</font>

117
00:12:36,176 --> 00:12:37,576
<font color=#FFFF2D>Two.</font>

118
00:12:39,145 --> 00:12:41,652
<font color=#FFFF2D>They were speaking at the same time.</font>

119
00:12:43,016 --> 00:12:45,604
<font color=#FFFF2D>Are you sure they had mouths...</font>

120
00:12:45,605 --> 00:12:48,590
<font color=#FFFF2D>How would you approach translating this?</font>

121
00:12:49,948 --> 00:12:53,434
<font color=#FFFF2D>You hear any words? Phrases?</font>

122
00:12:55,237 --> 00:12:57,714
<font color=#FFFF2D>I do not... I do not know.</font>

123
00:12:58,415 --> 00:12:59,904
<font color=#FFFF2D>So what can you tell?</font>

124
00:13:00,205 --> 00:13:04,157
<font color=#FFFF2D>I can tell you that it is impossible to
translate an audio file.</font>

125
00:13:04,158 --> 00:13:07,309
<font color=#FFFF2D>I would need to be there
to interact with them.</font>

126
00:13:07,821 --> 00:13:10,710
<font color=#FFFF2D>You did not need that for Farsi translation.</font>

127
00:13:10,711 --> 00:13:14,352
<font color=#FFFF2D>I did not need because I already
knew the language, but this is...</font>

128
00:13:18,588 --> 00:13:20,303
<font color=#FFFF2D>I know what you're doing.</font>

129
00:13:20,304 --> 00:13:22,865
<font color=#FFFF2D>- Tell me what Im doing.
- I'll not take you to Montana.</font>

130
00:13:23,166 --> 00:13:26,569
<font color=#FFFF2D>Its all I can do to keep it turning into a tourist site for everybody who has a (TH?) clearance.</font>

131
00:13:26,570 --> 00:13:29,377
<font color=#FFFF2D>Im just telling you what it would take
to do this job.</font>

132
00:13:29,378 --> 00:13:31,063
<font color=#FFFF2D>It is not a negotiation.</font>

133
00:13:31,864 --> 00:13:35,055
<font color=#FFFF2D>If I leave here... your chance is gone.</font>

134
00:13:43,101 --> 00:13:44,501
<font color=#FFFF2D>Good day.</font>

135
00:13:45,202 --> 00:13:46,642
<font color=#FFFF2D>Colonel...</font>

136
00:13:48,653 --> 00:13:52,503
<font color=#FFFF2D>You mentioned Berkeley.
Are you going to ask Danvers next?</font>

137
00:13:52,504 --> 00:13:53,904
<font color=#FFFF2D>Maybe.</font>

138
00:13:54,305 --> 00:13:56,046
<font color=#FFFF2D>Before you commit to him...</font>

139
00:13:56,347 --> 00:13:59,782
<font color=#FFFF2D>ask him the Sanskrit word for "war"
and its translation.</font>

140
00:14:07,783 --> 00:14:10,410
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>An agreement on sharing
scientific discoveries</font></i>

141
00:14:10,411 --> 00:14:14,976
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>Was closer tonight as Russia and China
***** at the United Nations.</font></i>

142
00:14:14,977 --> 00:14:18,760
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>Meanwhile, financial markets
across the world are in crisis</font></i>

143
00:14:18,761 --> 00:14:23,096
<i><font color=#FFFF2D>with the Dow Jones industrial average
fell 2,000 points...</font></i>

144
00:14:25,725 --> 00:14:28,525
<i><font color=#00FF40>(Chopper approaches)</font></i>

145
00:14:39,725 --> 00:14:42,300
<font color=#FFFF2D>- Good Morning.
- Colonel?</font>

146
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:46,315
<font color=#FFFF2D>Gavisti.
He says that means discussion.</font>

147
00:14:46,316 --> 00:14:49,828
<font color=#FFFF2D>- What you say means?
- A desire for more cows.</font>

148
00:14:49,829 --> 00:14:51,329
<font color=#FFFF2D>Pack your bags.</font>

149
00:14:52,834 --> 00:14:55,740
<font color=#FFFF2D>- All right, give me 20 minutes.
- Take only 10!</font>

150
00:14:56,901 --> 00:14:59,636
<font color=#FFFF2D>Dr. Banks! This way, please.</font>

151
00:15:26,937 --> 00:15:29,823
<font color=#FFFF2D>- Are you alright?
- Yes.</font>

152
00:15:58,023 --> 00:16:01,023
<i><font color=#00FF40>Inaudible dialogue due to
noise inside the chopper)</font></i>

153
00:16:04,926 --> 00:16:06,326
<font color=#FFFF2D>Thanks.</font>

154
00:16:09,527 --> 00:16:11,763
<font color=#FFFF2D>Sorry. Couldn't hear what you were saying.</font>

155
00:16:12,464 --> 00:16:15,243
<font color=#FFFF2D>"Language is the foundation
of civilization...</font>

156
00:16:15,244 --> 00:16:18,008
<font color=#FFFF2D>...It is the glue that holds
the people together...</font>

157
00:16:18,009 --> 00:16:20,649
<font color=#FFFF2D>...It is the first weapon
drawn in a conflict. "</font>

158
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:26,223
<font color=#FFFF2D>Louise, esse Ian Donnelly.
Louise Banks, Ian Donnelly.</font>

159
00:16:26,224 --> 00:16:29,023
<font color=#FFFF2D>- Quite a reading!
- Yeah...you wrote it.</font>

160
00:16:29,424 --> 00:16:30,824
<font color=#FFFF2D>Yeah.</font>

161
00:16:30,825 --> 00:16:33,286
<font color=#FFFF2D>It's the kind of thing
you write as a preface.</font>

162
00:16:33,287 --> 00:16:36,439
<font color=#FFFF2D>Dabbled with the basics.</font>

163
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:38,733
<font color=#FFFF2D>It's great. Even if its wrong.</font>

164
00:16:39,634 --> 00:16:43,159
<font color=#FFFF2D>- Its wrong?
- The cornerstone of civilization</font>

165
00:16:43,160 --> 00:16:44,623
<font color=#FFFF2D>isn't language - its science.</font>

166
00:16:45,224 --> 00:16:48,845
<font color=#FFFF2D>Ian is a theoretical physicist
at Los Alamos.</font>

167
00:16:49,434 --> 00:16:52,609
<font color=#FFFF2D>You'll report to me, but will be working
with him when you are in the shop.</font>

168
00:16:53,436 --> 00:16:55,390
<font color=#FFFF2D>Thats what they are calling the UFO?</font>

169
00:16:55,391 --> 00:16:58,979
<font color=#FFFF2D>Priority One. What do they want,
Where are they from?</font>

170
00:16:58,980 --> 00:17:01,398
<font color=#FFFF2D>Beyond that, how did they get here?</font>

171
00:17:01,399 --> 00:17:04,050
<font color=#FFFF2D>Are they capable of faster
than light travel?</font>

172
00:17:04,051 --> 00:17:07,655
<font color=#FFFF2D>I made a list of questions</font>

173
00:17:07,656 --> 00:17:11,100
<font color=#FFFF2D>ranging from handshakes
to binary sequences...</font>

174
00:17:11,101 --> 00:17:12,741
<font color=#FFFF2D>How about we just talk to them</font>

175
00:17:12,742 --> 00:17:15,292
<font color=#FFFF2D>before we start throwing problem at them?</font>

176
00:17:17,296 --> 00:17:19,284
<font color=#FFFF2D>That's why you both are here.</font>

177
00:17:21,506 --> 00:17:22,974
<font color=#FFFF2D>I'll bring the coffee.</font>

178
00:17:25,372 --> 00:17:27,159
<font color=#FFFF2D>Coffee with some aliens.</font>

179
00:19:37,947 --> 00:19:41,524
<font color=#FFFF2D>- Take them to Dr. Kettler.
- Yes sir.</font>

180
00:19:41,525 --> 00:19:43,225
<font color=#FFFF2D>Follow the Captain to the Medical Wing.</font>

181
00:19:43,226 --> 00:19:45,999
<font color=#FFFF2D>The procedure takes just a few minutes,
then we'll start.</font>

182
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:47,400
<font color=#FFFF2D>Alright.</font>

183
00:19:57,822 --> 00:20:01,172
<font color=#FFFF2D>They will take care of your bags...</font>

184
00:20:01,816 --> 00:20:03,216
<font color=#FFFF2D>and cell phones.</font>

185
00:20:04,422 --> 00:20:05,822
<font color=#FFFF2D>Follow me.</font>

186
00:20:06,482 --> 00:20:08,680
<font color=#FFFF2D>Put this on and wear them all times.</font>

187
00:20:21,966 --> 00:20:23,366
<font color=#FFFF2D>Sir, they're here.</font>

188
00:20:24,025 --> 00:20:26,000
