<font color=#26F70F>(Alarms sounding)</font>

673
01:08:20,061 --> 01:08:25,161
<font color=#26F70F>(People conversing)</font>

674
01:08:39,156 --> 01:08:40,743
What did they say?

675
01:08:41,515 --> 01:08:44,380
China and Russia are off the grid.
They aren't speaking very well.

676
01:08:44,381 --> 01:08:47,430
What they learnt in the last session
has them spooked.

677
01:08:49,864 --> 01:08:51,627
Yes sir.

678
01:08:51,628 --> 01:08:53,374
We have orders to do the same.

679
01:08:53,375 --> 01:08:56,519
- Wait these are our allies!
- Put your radio on silence!

680
01:08:56,520 --> 01:08:59,608
- Do it.
- We received a message from the heptá...

681
01:09:00,303 --> 01:09:01,891
Damn it!

682
01:09:02,235 --> 01:09:04,656
We need to be talking to each other!

683
01:09:04,856 --> 01:09:07,356
You want to talk to them?
Find out what this means.

684
01:09:14,701 --> 01:09:16,812
<font color=#26F70F>(Man on radio)This cam is now offline...</font>

685
01:09:21,606 --> 01:09:24,034
We've never re-entered the session before.

686
01:09:24,035 --> 01:09:26,695
Louise, trust me ok? We got time.

687
01:09:26,696 --> 01:09:28,626
Just gotta step on it, alright?

688
01:09:29,360 --> 01:09:30,964
<b><font color=#C752ED>"USE WEAPON"</font></b>

689
01:09:30,965 --> 01:09:34,553
This is the alien message sent to provoke

690
01:09:34,554 --> 01:09:38,567
the Chinese government to withdraw their
scientists from the international mission today.

691
01:09:38,568 --> 01:09:41,053
In a statement, General Shang said:

692
01:09:41,054 --> 01:09:43,066
"China no longer trusts the aliens

693
01:09:43,067 --> 01:09:44,651
who wants to divide us.

694
01:09:44,652 --> 01:09:46,724
Humanity must be protected. "

695
01:09:46,725 --> 01:09:49,781
China has asked for immediate
talks at the UN.

696
01:09:52,964 --> 01:09:55,725
<font color=#26F70F>(Man on comm)
Alpha 1-9, this is Condor. Over.</font>

697
01:09:59,946 --> 01:10:04,104
<font color=#26F70F>Alpha 1-9, this is Condor. Come in. Over.</font>

698
01:10:09,241 --> 01:10:12,582
<font color=#26F70F>Captain Marks, Condor, not receiving a transmission.</font>

699
01:10:12,583 --> 01:10:14,447
<font color=#26F70F>Let me know if you are listening.</font>

700
01:10:15,381 --> 01:10:19,730
<font color=#26F70F>Capt. Marks, all escorts are
ordered to cease all activites...</font>

701
01:10:39,196 --> 01:11:40,696
<b><font color=#FF80FF>video has jumped back to 00:42:15 mins
Not subbing this again. Jump to 01:39:06</font></b>

702
01:39:15,329 --> 01:39:17,579
No, no, no...
Dr. Banks you can't go in there.

703
01:39:17,580 --> 01:39:20,290
- Just need to ask one question.
- Dr. Banks!

704
01:39:20,676 --> 01:39:23,944
The session is closed.
You can't go back in, it's dangerous...

705
01:39:23,945 --> 01:39:26,254
We just need 5 minutes. No sweat.

706
01:39:26,474 --> 01:39:27,995
Morris, Let him go.

707
01:39:30,441 --> 01:39:32,195
Hey, Abbott.

708
01:39:37,162 --> 01:39:40,432
So, what are calling our session?
Session 37?

709
01:39:40,885 --> 01:39:44,474
- No 36 Part 2
- Ok.

710
01:39:50,579 --> 01:39:52,007
Why are you alone?

711
01:39:52,008 --> 01:39:53,977
Been attempting to call Capt. Marks.

712
01:39:53,978 --> 01:39:57,570
- The escorts not responding.
- Why not?

713
01:39:58,182 --> 01:39:59,588
Send security.

714
01:40:02,687 --> 01:40:06,147
Offer a weapon... question mark.

715
01:40:10,957 --> 01:40:13,013
They are offering us something.

716
01:40:22,430 --> 01:40:25,506
Technology, device, method...

717
01:40:25,507 --> 01:40:27,823
See this? This is a different word.

718
01:40:27,824 --> 01:40:30,890
This... this segment is a lot busier.

719
01:40:35,731 --> 01:40:39,385
Give... technology...

720
01:40:40,718 --> 01:40:42,162
... Now.

721
01:40:50,574 --> 01:40:52,140
Whats he doing?

722
01:40:57,793 --> 01:41:00,404
Capt. ****** check.

723
01:41:08,783 --> 01:41:10,901
security team coming, sir.

724
01:41:10,902 --> 01:41:13,895
4 minutes remain.
We must see this through.

725
01:41:14,295 --> 01:41:16,144
Come on. Download weapons.

726
01:41:16,145 --> 01:41:18,957
- Fire *******.
- Understood.

727
01:41:18,958 --> 01:41:20,371
We will open shooting soon.

728
01:41:20,372 --> 01:41:23,906
To be no casualties.

729
01:41:50,690 --> 01:41:53,158
Abbott wants me to write on the barrier.

730
01:41:58,543 --> 01:42:00,643
Can you even do that?

731
01:42:01,243 --> 01:42:02,727
I don't know.

732
01:42:06,127 --> 01:42:08,127
<font color=#26F70F>(places writing the ground)</font>

733
01:42:18,830 --> 01:42:20,978
I can't do it with both hands.

734
01:42:21,178 --> 01:42:22,178
<font color=#26F70F>(Background music)</font>

735
01:43:32,160 --> 01:43:33,747
Louise.

736
01:43:49,425 --> 01:43:50,852
What is that?

737
01:44:35,699 --> 01:44:38,381
Hey...Hey...Hey... Take it easy.

738
01:44:38,382 --> 01:44:41,367
You suffered a concussion.
Just lay back.

739
01:44:44,158 --> 01:44:46,047
How you feeling?

740
01:44:54,517 --> 01:44:57,684
- How is Ian?
- Well, same as you. He is ok.

741
01:44:59,474 --> 01:45:02,273
- Who... who did this?
- Some soldiers.

742
01:45:04,049 --> 01:45:06,169
Been watching too much TV.

743
01:45:09,438 --> 01:45:12,869
- What is that?
- take it easy... take it easy

744
01:45:12,870 --> 01:45:16,831
The place is no longer secure.
We're on standby to evacuate.

745
01:45:16,832 --> 01:45:18,493
Where is Ian?

746
01:45:19,114 --> 01:45:21,828
Weber came and got him maybe 10 minutes ago.

747
01:45:22,140 --> 01:45:25,115
He wouldn't leave till
he knew you were okay.

748
01:45:28,149 --> 01:45:32,649
The whole tent is on the clock to figure
out whatever it is you were given up there.

749
01:45:38,196 --> 01:45:39,752
This is all of it?

750
01:45:40,200 --> 01:45:42,803
The feed wasn't interrupted
by the explosion.

751
01:45:43,448 --> 01:45:45,361
Thats right.

752
01:45:47,374 --> 01:45:50,287
- You see something?
- I don't know yet.

753
01:45:50,605 --> 01:45:53,570
I need my team get together
with Louise's team.

754
01:45:53,571 --> 01:45:56,411
- I need everyone working on this.
- We can not leave.

755
01:45:56,412 --> 01:45:58,552
- Glad to see you awake.
- We need to go back in there

756
01:45:58,553 --> 01:46:00,641
and explain to them that
this wasn't our fault.

757
01:46:00,642 --> 01:46:02,602
- We can't go back inside.
- We have to!

758
01:46:02,993 --> 01:46:04,906
What happened in there was an attack.

759
01:46:04,907 --> 01:46:07,783
We can hope for the best,
but we have to prepare for retaliation.

760
01:46:07,784 --> 01:46:09,260
we may have to evacuate...

761
01:46:09,261 --> 01:46:12,850
Thats a wrong move.
As long as they stay, we have to stay.

762
01:46:46,827 --> 01:46:48,922
Well, they are not leaving.

763
01:46:50,630 --> 01:46:52,896
Why does it feel worse?

764
01:46:57,418 --> 01:46:59,085
China is on the offensive.

765
01:46:59,184 --> 01:47:02,994
They are positioning their military to blow
the alien vessel right out of the sky.

766
01:47:02,995 --> 01:47:06,415
If this happens, we can't sit
and wait for their retaliation.

767
01:47:06,616 --> 01:47:08,171
So get prepared.

768
01:47:08,172 --> 01:47:11,101
The Air Force and Infantry are standing by.

769
01:47:11,915 --> 01:47:13,992
<b><font color=#FF71FF>BREAKING NEWS</font></b>

770
01:47:13,993 --> 01:47:17,295
Tonight, China becomes the first world power

771
01:47:17,296 --> 01:47:20,097
To declare war against the aliens.

772
01:47:20,098 --> 01:47:23,665
Following the failure of the diplomatic
efforts of the United Nations,

773
01:47:23,666 --> 01:47:26,989
China confirmed that its language experts
tonight...

774
01:47:26,990 --> 01:47:30,389
delivered an ultimatum at the Shanghai site.

775
01:47:30,390 --> 01:47:31,790
In a televised statement,

776
01:47:31,791 --> 01:47:34,654
Gen. Shang, chairman of the
People's Liberation Army,

777
01:47:34,655 --> 01:47:38,555
Said the aliens have 24 hours to
leave Chinese territory,

778
01:47:38,556 --> 01:47:40,330
or face destruction.

779
01:47:40,331 --> 01:47:42,127
And he urged all other world leaders

780
01:47:42,128 --> 01:47:45,432
to unite with China and
take a similar stance.

781
01:47:46,129 --> 01:47:49,550
With a huge build up of forces
at their landing sites,

782
01:47:49,551 --> 01:47:51,830
Pakistan, Russia and Sudan

783
01:47:51,831 --> 01:47:54,266
Are thought to be following China's lead.

784
01:48:09,962 --> 01:48:11,922
It can't be random.

785
01:48:27,577 --> 01:48:29,475
Its going to take us years.

786
01:48:34,734 --> 01:48:36,488
Whats this term here?

787
01:48:40,209 --> 01:48:41,820
Mum.

788
01:48:44,267 --> 01:48:46,588
- Mother?
- Hm?

789
01:48:46,589 --> 01:48:49,975
- sweetie?
- Whats this term for that thing...

790
01:48:49,976 --> 01:48:51,983
Like a technical term...

791
01:48:51,984 --> 01:48:55,526
When we make a deal and we
both get something out of it?

792
01:48:55,527 --> 01:48:58,773
- A compromise?
- No...

793
01:48:59,093 --> 01:49:01,493
Like it's competition,

794
01:49:01,494 --> 01:49:04,089
But both sides end up happy.

795
01:49:05,378 --> 01:49:07,530
And win-win?

796
01:49:07,531 --> 01:49:09,603
more sciency than that.

797
01:49:09,604 --> 01:49:11,961
If you want science, call your father.

798
01:49:26,613 --> 01:49:28,034
Thank you.

799
01:49:38,536 --> 01:49:39,993
Sorry.

800
01:49:40,337 --> 01:49:43,028
Its okay.

801
01:49:47,748 --> 01:49:49,232
What time is it?

802
01:49:50,680 --> 01:49:53,458
Its time to open the bottle
you've been hiding.

803
01:49:57,273 --> 01:49:59,439
You cracked something, didn't you?

804
01:49:59,793 --> 01:50:01,975
Yeah. Come here.

805
01:50:02,708 --> 01:50:07,053
Take a look at this section.
It seems to be talking about time.

806
01:50:07,054 --> 01:50:10,585
You see the symbol of "time" - everywhere.

807
01:50:10,586 --> 01:50:12,519
So what is this?

808
01:50:13,150 --> 01:50:15,880
A formula for faster than light travel?

809
01:50:16,510 --> 01:50:18,026
Who can tell?

810
01:50:18,782 --> 01:50:21,807
It has too many gaps.
Its not complete.

811
01:50:21,808 --> 01:50:23,220
Then it dawned on me.

812
01:50:26,307 --> 01:50:27,743
Right here.

813
01:50:28,800 --> 01:50:31,553
Stop focussing on the "1"s.
Look at the "0"s.

814
01:50:31,722 --> 01:50:35,327
How much of it is data and
how much of it is negative space?

815
01:50:36,498 --> 01:50:38,093
So I measured it.

816
01:50:39,980 --> 01:50:42,964
0.0833 recurring.

817
01:50:48,139 --> 01:50:50,353
Perhaps you'd like to add
that as a fraction.

818
01:50:53,623 --> 01:50:55,274
1/12.

819
01:50:58,173 --> 01:51:02,005
What is saying right here, is that,
this is one of twelfth.

820
01:51:02,106 --> 01:51:05,855
- We are part of a larger hole.
- Or 1 of 12 contestants for the prize.

821
01:51:05,856 --> 01:51:08,603
- Why do we have to talk to him?
- We all working together here.

822
01:51:08,604 --> 01:51:13,122
We need to talk to the other sites,
We need to help them with what they got from the other Heptápodes.

823
01:51:13,123 --> 01:51:15,372
In case you don't remember,
we're blacked out.

824
01:51:15,373 --> 01:51:18,107
China just threatened to destroy
their Shell. We are on our own.

825
01:51:18,108 --> 01:51:19,972
But it says that all the pieces fit in.

826
01:51:19,973 --> 01:51:22,162
And I'm telling you that no one else cares.

827
01:51:22,750 --> 01:51:26,136
Two hours ago we pulled this audio off
a secured channel in Russia.

828
01:51:26,137 --> 01:51:28,892
Someone from their science team
was broadcasting live.

829
01:51:31,054 --> 01:51:33,955
<font color=#20DE1B>(voice on recorder)In their final session,
the alien said:</font>

830
01:51:33,956 --> 01:51:37,225
<font color=#20DE1B>"There's no time. Many become one..."</font>

831
01:51:37,873 --> 01:51:40,223
<font color=#20DE1B>I feel we have all the given weapons.</font>

832
01:51:40,224 --> 01:51:42,351
<font color=#20DE1B>If anyone is receiving this...</font>

833
01:51:42,884 --> 01:51:44,543
<font color=#20DE1B>Please...</font>

834
01:51:44,743 --> 01:51:45,743
<font color=#20DE1B>(sound of gunshot)</font>

835
01:51:49,662 --> 01:51:51,456
Well, I mean...

836
01:51:52,334 --> 01:51:54,858
There are a lot of ways you can
interpret what he said.

837
01:51:54,859 --> 01:51:57,256
I don't need an interpreter to
know what this means.

838
01:51:57,257 --> 01:52:00,770
Russia just executed one of their own
experts to keep their secret.

839
01:52:00,771 --> 01:52:02,989
"Many become one"
can be their way of saying

840
01:52:02,990 --> 01:52:05,022
Some only required.

841
01:52:05,023 --> 01:52:08,478
Why hand it out to us in pieces?
Why not give it all?

842
01:52:08,479 --> 01:52:11,212
What better way to force us
to work together for once?

843
01:52:11,842 --> 01:52:13,288
Even if I did believe you,

844
01:52:13,289 --> 01:52:17,185
How in the world are you going to get anyone
else to play along, and give out their data?

845
01:52:18,012 --> 01:52:20,028
- We offer ours in return.
- yeah?

846
01:52:22,184 --> 01:52:25,224
- What, trade?
- Its a non zero sum game.

847
01:52:27,965 --> 01:52:29,780
Non zero sum game.

848
01:52:31,145 --> 01:52:34,393
Thats it. Thanks.

849
01:52:41,618 --> 01:52:44,782
9 local completely isolated.

850
01:52:45,358 --> 01:52:49,089
Only way to reach them is to physically drive and
yell at the border guards which we are doing.

851
01:52:49,090 --> 01:52:50,517
But it won't be fast enough.

852
01:52:50,518 --> 01:52:52,948
There must be a way to get the message.

853
01:52:52,949 --> 01:52:55,789
To our allies, maybe. But at this stage,
it's little too late.

854
01:52:55,790 --> 01:52:59,181
What we need is to get all the
other nations online...

855
01:52:59,182 --> 01:53:03,010
before we start a war and theres
no way for us to reach them

856
01:53:03,011 --> 01:53:05,607
Wait. Hold on a second.
Louise.

857
01:53:06,585 --> 01:53:08,331
Its right above us.

858
01:53:09,047 --> 01:53:11,152
Thats problematic for us right now.

859
01:53:11,153 --> 01:53:13,978
The Pentagon is convinced
that our Shell will retaliate.

860
01:53:13,979 --> 01:53:16,728
I'd guess its orders say that we leave
within the hour.

861
01:53:17,834 --> 01:53:21,244
Look they are not our enemy.
They meant no act of aggression towards us.

862
01:53:21,245 --> 01:53:23,325
Maybe thats their way of being aggressive.

863
01:53:23,326 --> 01:53:26,439
- Its not the question.
- Then what is the question?

864
01:53:27,055 --> 01:53:30,600
How do we get you back in that room
thats half a mile straight up?

865
01:53:30,942 --> 01:53:32,569
I think our work here is done.

866
01:53:33,454 --> 01:53:36,137
Its in the hands of our superiors now.

867
01:53:56,271 --> 01:53:58,271
What the hell is she doing?

868
01:55:06,171 --> 01:55:08,371
<font color=#20DE1B>(Coughing)</font>

869
01:55:13,071 --> 01:55:15,971
<font color=#20DE1B>(Door opening)</font>

870
01:55:56,496 --> 01:55:58,196
<font color=#20DE1B>(breathing)</font>

871
01:57:14,696 --> 01:57:16,419
Costello?

872
01:57:18,763 --> 01:57:20,493
Where is Abbott?

873
01:57:30,483 --> 01:57:33,618
<font color=#EF65FE>"ABBOTT IS DEATH PROCESS"</font>

874
01:57:50,094 --> 01:57:51,530
I'm sorry.

875
01:57:53,758 --> 01:57:55,400
We're sorry.

876
01:57:59,735 --> 01:58:01,728
I need you to...

877
01:58:02,802 --> 01:58:06,487
I need you to... to send a message...
to the other sites.

878
01:58:12,560 --> 01:58:15,885
<font color=#FF6CFF>LOUISE HAS WEAPON</font>

879
01:58:23,856 --> 01:58:25,514
<font color=#FF6CFF>"USE WEAPON"</font>

880
01:58:25,515 --> 01:58:29,201
I don't... I don't understand.

881
01:58:29,605 --> 01:58:33,058
What is your purpose here?

882
01:58:39,695 --> 01:58:42,893
<font color=#FF6CFF>"WE HELP HUMANITY"</font>

883
01:58:48,333 --> 01:58:51,245
<font color=#FF6CFF>"IN THREE THOUSAND YEARS"</font>

884
01:58:53,782 --> 01:58:57,258
<font color=#FF6CFF>"WE NEED HUMANITY HELP"</font>

885
01:58:59,705 --> 01:59:02,062
How can you know the future?

886
01:59:18,706 --> 01:59:20,699
I don't...

887
01:59:21,784 --> 01:59:25,887
I don't understand. Who is this child?

888
01:59:31,124 --> 01:59:34,394
The program is called
"Mommy and Daddy talk to animals."

889
01:59:46,767 --> 01:59:49,846
<font color=#FF6CFF>"LOUISE SEES FUTURE"</font>

890
02:00:00,568 --> 02:00:03,306
<font color=#FF6CFF>"WEAPON OPENS TIME"</font>

891
02:00:09,083 --> 02:00:12,057
Wait... No! Wait!

892
02:01:01,182 --> 02:01:02,582
- Dr. Banks!
- Louise!

893
02:01:02,583 --> 02:01:04,193
Are you alright?

894
02:01:07,300 --> 02:01:09,418
- You alright?
- Yeah.

895
02:01:09,419 --> 02:01:11,141
Come here.

896
02:01:11,142 --> 02:01:12,946
I tried to understand. But they...

897
02:01:12,947 --> 02:01:15,512
It doesn't matter now.
We have orders to evacuate.

898
02:01:15,681 --> 02:01:17,398
- Why?
- Russia and Sudan

899
02:01:17,399 --> 02:01:18,852
will follow suit.

900
02:01:21,585 --> 02:01:23,837
Ian... I do not understand why...?

901
02:01:23,838 --> 02:01:25,834
Help me, Mama.

902
02:01:25,835 --> 02:01:27,492
Louise...

903
02:01:28,323 --> 02:01:29,783
Mom!

904
02:01:31,933 --> 02:01:33,497
Momma!

905
02:01:35,927 --> 02:01:37,879
Sorry, honey.

906
02:01:41,028 --> 02:01:43,322
What day is it, do you know baby?

907
02:01:43,323 --> 02:01:44,871
Sunday.

908
02:01:50,369 --> 02:01:52,917
Are you gonna leave me like Daddy did?

909
02:01:53,328 --> 02:01:56,566
Oh, Hannah, honey,
your daddy didn't leave you.

910
02:01:57,402 --> 02:01:59,751
You're gonna see him... this weekend.

911
02:02:00,730 --> 02:02:03,532
He never look me anymore.

912
02:02:11,797 --> 02:02:13,654
Its my fault.

913
02:02:15,706 --> 02:02:18,952
I told him something that
he wasn't ready to hear.

914
02:02:20,789 --> 02:02:22,463
What?

915
02:02:24,122 --> 02:02:25,566
Well...

916
02:02:26,203 --> 02:02:28,124
Believe it or not...

917
02:02:28,571 --> 02:02:31,198
I know something thats going to happen.

918
02:02:33,433 --> 02:02:36,322
I can not explain how I know it,
I just do.

919
02:02:37,606 --> 02:02:40,852
And when I told your daddy, he
got really mad.

920
02:02:42,692 --> 02:02:45,057
He said I made the wrong choice.

921
02:02:47,631 --> 02:02:50,655
What? Whats going to happen?

922
02:02:53,481 --> 02:02:55,586
It has to do with a...

923
02:02:55,587 --> 02:02:57,333
A very rare disease.

924
02:03:00,342 --> 02:03:02,477
And its unstoppable.

925
02:03:04,308 --> 02:03:06,340
Kind of like you are.

926
02:03:06,908 --> 02:03:08,432
You're so amazing

927
02:03:09,306 --> 02:03:13,369
And your poetry and all the other amazing
things that you share with the world.

928
02:03:13,921 --> 02:03:18,166
- I'm unstoppable?
- Yeah.

929
02:03:35,064 --> 02:03:36,588
I got you...

930
02:03:38,082 --> 02:03:39,582
I got you.

931
02:03:40,187 --> 02:03:41,687
Louise.

932
02:03:43,219 --> 02:03:45,767
I just realized why my husband left me.

933
02:03:45,768 --> 02:03:47,516
My husband left me.

934
02:03:47,617 --> 02:03:49,070
You have been married?

935
02:03:50,303 --> 02:03:51,827
Let's get out of here.

936
02:04:25,027 --> 02:04:26,027
<font color=#00FF40>(chopper flying by)</font>

937
02:04:26,306 --> 02:04:28,191
- Mamma.
- Yeah?

938
02:04:28,937 --> 02:04:30,961
Why my name is Hannah?

939
02:04:36,406 --> 02:04:39,264
Your name is very special.

940
02:04:39,265 --> 02:04:41,457
Because it is a palindrome.

941
02:04:41,458 --> 02:04:45,048
It reads the same word from backwards.

942
02:04:45,689 --> 02:04:47,289
<font color=#00FF40>(conversation in the background)</font>

943
02:04:47,489 --> 02:04:50,677
- Turn it off.
- That goes back.

944
02:05:10,013 --> 02:05:12,100
<font color=#FF6CFF>"UNIVERSAL LANGUAGE"</font>

945
02:05:20,811 --> 02:05:21,811
<font color=#FF6CFF>"TO HANNAH"</font>

946
02:05:22,012 --> 02:05:23,255
Hey!

947
02:05:23,256 --> 02:05:25,169
We're done here.

948
02:05:25,601 --> 02:05:27,363
Let's take this with us.

949
02:05:32,110 --> 02:05:34,085
<font color=#FF6CFF>"UNIVERSAL LANGUAGE BY LOUISE BANKS"</font>

950
02:05:34,086 --> 02:05:35,625
<font color=#FF6CFF>TRANSLATING HEPTPODES</font>

951
02:05:50,603 --> 02:05:51,603
<font color=#00FF40>(Inaudible)</font>

952
02:05:51,803 --> 02:05:53,446
I can read it.

953
02:05:57,461 --> 02:05:59,116
- I know what it is.
- What?

954
02:05:59,117 --> 02:06:01,747
It's not a weapon. It's a gift.

955
02:06:02,226 --> 02:06:04,163
The weapon is their language.

956
02:06:04,164 --> 02:06:06,517
They gave it all to us.

957
02:06:06,518 --> 02:06:08,951
So we can learn Heptápode?

958
02:06:08,952 --> 02:06:11,888
If you learn it... really learn it,

959
02:06:12,035 --> 02:06:14,735
you get to perceive time the way they do.

960
02:06:14,736 --> 02:06:17,352
So you get to see whats to happen.

961
02:06:17,353 --> 02:06:20,185
But time, it isn't the same for them.

962
02:06:20,186 --> 02:06:22,439
- It is not linear.
- Look...

963
02:06:22,440 --> 02:06:24,874
We did our best but it wasn't enough.

964
02:06:25,791 --> 02:06:29,437
The captain will lift off in 5 minutes.

965
02:06:29,618 --> 02:06:33,408
Ian, Louise... It was an honor
to work with you.

966
02:06:34,115 --> 02:06:35,723
Good luck.

967
02:06:38,896 --> 02:06:40,574
Colonel...

968
02:06:47,259 --> 02:06:49,040
I'll find out where we are going.

969
02:06:57,398 --> 02:06:59,509
Wake up, Mummy.

970
02:07:34,928 --> 02:07:36,674
Dr. Banks...

971
02:07:37,656 --> 02:07:39,116
Its a pleasure.

972
02:07:39,446 --> 02:07:42,835
General Shang, the pleasure is mine.

973
02:07:43,345 --> 02:07:45,051
Your president said...

974
02:07:45,488 --> 02:07:48,767
It was an honor to host me in celebration.

975
02:07:48,768 --> 02:07:51,086
- Of course.
- I confess...

976
02:07:51,545 --> 02:07:54,878
The only reason why I am here is...

977
02:07:55,739 --> 02:07:57,564
To meet you in person.

978
02:07:58,591 --> 02:08:01,620
Well, Im flattered. Thank you.

979
02:08:02,118 --> 02:08:06,520
18 months ago, you did something remarkable.

980
02:08:07,273 --> 02:08:11,146
Something not even my superior has done.

981
02:08:12,614 --> 02:08:16,114
- What's that?
- You changed my mind.

982
02:08:18,113 --> 02:08:22,232
You are the reason for this unification.

983
02:08:22,840 --> 02:08:26,499
All because you reached out to
me on my private number.

984
02:08:28,952 --> 02:08:32,428
Your private number?
General I do not know your private number...

985
02:08:39,705 --> 02:08:41,329
Now you know.

986
02:08:43,569 --> 02:08:47,061
I claimed to know how your mind works,
but...

987
02:08:47,714 --> 02:08:51,277
I believe it was important
for you to see that.

988
02:08:52,783 --> 02:08:55,069
I called you tonight?

989
02:08:55,582 --> 02:08:57,162
Yes, you did.

990
02:09:09,350 --> 02:09:10,866
Louise...

991
02:09:26,653 --> 02:09:29,027
Alright, let's shut down the system.

992
02:09:29,028 --> 02:09:33,020
Sir... there's a satelite
here dialling China.

993
02:09:35,368 --> 02:09:36,951
Here? What do you mean here?

994
02:09:39,230 --> 02:09:41,048
Come on, answer.

995
02:09:42,052 --> 02:09:43,672
Whose phone is it?

996
02:09:47,823 --> 02:09:49,458
It's your phone, sir.

997
02:09:56,361 --> 02:09:58,331
Search base camp now.

998
02:09:58,332 --> 02:10:00,427
Find out who is using that phone.

999
02:10:00,428 --> 02:10:03,080
- Hold on to those co-ordinates.
- Yes sir.

1000
02:10:03,081 --> 02:10:05,962
C'mon... What am I saying?

1001
02:10:06,446 --> 02:10:08,262
What am I saying?

1002
02:10:09,010 --> 02:10:10,454
okay.

1003
02:10:18,732 --> 02:10:20,201
okay.

1004
02:10:21,292 --> 02:10:24,193
I never forget what you said.

1005
02:10:34,739 --> 02:10:38,168
You told me my wife's dying words.

1006
02:10:55,607 --> 02:10:57,141
We found the source of the phone call.

1007
02:10:57,142 --> 02:10:59,402
It is in decontamination.
Waiting for instructions.

1008
02:11:00,948 --> 02:11:02,960
Louise... What are you doing?

1009
02:11:04,048 --> 02:11:06,309
- What are you doing?
- Changing his opinion.

1010
02:11:06,310 --> 02:11:07,710
Buy us 20 seconds.

1011
02:11:07,711 --> 02:11:09,411
- We do not have time.
- Trust me.

1012
02:11:09,412 --> 02:11:12,352
- 20 seconds. Do you trust me?
- Now? It's all right.

1013
02:11:15,264 --> 02:11:17,059
Dr. Banks...

1014
02:11:17,060 --> 02:11:19,036
Drop the phone, or we shoot.

1015
02:11:21,977 --> 02:11:24,561
- Drop it!
- Im sorry!

1016
02:11:27,071 --> 02:11:29,142
This is an act of treason!

1017
02:11:35,254 --> 02:11:37,024
- Drop it!
- Its done.

1018
02:11:37,025 --> 02:11:38,515
I got it.

1019
02:11:52,844 --> 02:11:56,044
The communications blackout
from all 12 landing sites...

1020
02:11:56,045 --> 02:11:58,378
continues this evening...

1021
02:11:58,379 --> 02:12:01,791
<font color=#00FF40>(news)Hold on... We are just hearing.</font>

1022
02:12:01,792 --> 02:12:04,355
- We are going to cut this report to tell you.
- Latest news.

1023
02:12:04,356 --> 02:12:06,649
China has called an emergency
press conference...

1024
02:12:06,650 --> 02:12:09,956
General Shang, chief of the
People's Liberation Army...

1025
02:12:09,957 --> 02:12:14,158
Has announced in an emergency press
conference that China is standing down.

1026
02:12:14,159 --> 02:12:17,079
China is stating that all the intelligence
they have received...

1027
02:12:17,080 --> 02:12:19,774
Will be shared immediately...

1028
02:12:20,052 --> 02:12:22,551
The world is entering a new era...

1029
02:12:22,552 --> 02:12:25,347
The Russian army are now revealing

1030
02:12:25,348 --> 02:12:29,470
information they acquired
from both their landing sites...

1031
02:12:29,471 --> 02:12:33,222
The 12 pieces of the puzzle is
slowly being put together.

1032
02:14:22,109 --> 02:14:25,409
So, Hannah...

1033
02:14:26,195 --> 02:14:28,685
This is where your story begins.

1034
02:14:30,794 --> 02:14:32,865
The day they departed.

1035
02:14:36,855 --> 02:14:38,530
Are you alright?

1036
02:14:41,628 --> 02:14:44,120
Despite knowing the journey...

1037
02:14:44,432 --> 02:14:46,337
and where it leads...

1038
02:14:49,080 --> 02:14:50,866
I embrace it.

1039
02:14:53,261 --> 02:14:56,531
And I welcome every moment of it.

1040
02:15:11,287 --> 02:15:15,977
H-A-N-N-A-H.

1041
02:15:29,686 --> 02:15:31,543
Now backwards.

1042
02:15:31,544 --> 02:15:35,062
H-A-N-N-A-H.

1043
02:15:35,063 --> 02:15:36,574
Hannah.

1044
02:15:36,575 --> 02:15:37,996
You ready, baby?

1045
02:15:41,155 --> 02:15:43,020
- Hey.
- Hey.

1046
02:15:43,674 --> 02:15:46,198
- It's okay?
- Yes you can go.

1047
02:15:48,780 --> 02:15:50,485
Daddy!

1048
02:15:59,620 --> 02:16:02,711
Are you ok?
I'll just roll over you.

1049
02:16:05,264 --> 02:16:07,256
Are you ready?

1050
02:16:11,214 --> 02:16:13,103
Guess what... All star stuff.

1051
02:16:15,237 --> 02:16:17,523
- Ian.
- Yeah.

1052
02:16:18,255 --> 02:16:21,517
If you see your whole life,
from start to finish...

1053
02:16:23,625 --> 02:16:25,760
Would you change things?

1054
02:16:31,741 --> 02:16:33,439
Maybe I...

1055
02:16:33,982 --> 02:16:37,089
I say what I feel more often. I don't know.

1056
02:16:52,959 --> 02:16:55,308
I've had my head tilted up to the stars

1057
02:16:55,309 --> 02:16:57,478
for as long as I can remember.

1058
02:16:59,640 --> 02:17:02,052
But you know what surprised me?

1059
02:17:04,000 --> 02:17:05,957
It was not meeting them.

1060
02:17:10,936 --> 02:17:12,627
It was meeting you.

1061
02:17:53,189 --> 02:17:56,277
I'd forgotten how good it felt
to be held by you.

1062
02:18:06,020 --> 02:18:07,837
Do you want to make a baby?

1063
02:18:44,184 --> 02:18:45,769
Yes... yeah!

1064
02:18:50,849 --> 02:18:53,849
<b><font color=#FC5652>Transcript by Cianide</font></b>

1065
02:19:00,099 --> 02:19:03,464
<b><font color=#FF6CFF>ARRIVAL</font></b>